description:
&lt;p&gt;Applications are invited from well-motivated individuals to work in a busy clinical microbiology laboratory based in a large NHS Trust. Well-equipped, with ISO: 15189:2012 accreditation and we have training status with the Health Care Professions Council (HCPC). We have a workload in excess of 700,000 tests per annum and offer a comprehensive range of tests in bacteriology, serology and virology, including molecular. In addition the department is testing around 3600 samples per week for Molecular CoVID19 and 1000 serology specimens.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be working in a modern, well-equiped facility performing a wide range of tasks providing support to Biomedical Scientists and Associate Practitioners in the provision of a high quality and efficient diagnostic Microbiology service. This will require you to have good hand to eye co-ordination, attention to detail and manual dexterity. Duties include assisting with the receipt and processing of clinical specimens, computer data entry and occasional use of autoclaves for the disposal of waste.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A sound general education (GCSE or equivalent in five subjects including English Language, Maths and preferably a Science subject) and experience with electronic handling of data are required. The post would suit someone who is a team player with good organisational skills. There is an element of manual handling involved.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Previous laboratory experience or an interest in biology is desirable and full training will be provided.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Working hours: 37.5 per week – the department operates core shifts (09:00-17:00) early shifts (08:00-16:00) and late shifts (12:00-20:00) as well as covering weekends and bank holidays. The post will rotate across all of these shift patterns.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;Closing Date: 11th November 2020&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
